  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>carrots</strong> and <strong>sweet potatoes</strong>, then&nbsp;chop them into bite-sized pieces</p>\r\n<p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> with the side of a knife, peel it and chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>brown onion</strong> and chop coarsely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2-4 tbsp of <strong>olive oil</strong> to a large pot on a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once the oil is hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3 min or until soft</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 750ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.5L]</span> of <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and stir to dissolve, then add the <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>sweet potato</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat and simmer for 20 min or until the carrots and potato are tender, stirring occasionally</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the contents of the pot using a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> for a smooth soup</p>\r\n<p>Tip: let the soup cool down a bit first and if you are not using a stick blender, only half fill the blender and hold the lid down firmly with a tea towel</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/106.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
